FOSSASIA is one of the top Free and Open Source Software
(FOSS) events for developers, enterprises, officials and 
general users in South East Asia. Each year in November it
takes place in Ho Chi Minh City (Saigon), Vietnam, attracting
speakers from across Asia and the world and over 1000 local 
participants. More than 130 volunteers support the event.
Over 50% of attendees are women. The event offers tracks for
numerous Open Source projects including the Linux community,
Android mobile developers and map developers. It features
sessions for newcomers to learn about Open Source tools such
as Open Document Office Suites or specialized workshops about
software translation. Please join us in Vietnam and become
part of an exciting community full of energy.
